'''Mithrobuzanes''' ({{lang-grc-gre|Μιθροβουζάνης}}; d. 334 BC) was a Persian governor (satrap) of [[Cappadocia (satrapy)|Cappadocia]] in the 4th century BC, during the reign of [[Darius III]]. He was probably a son of Ariarathes.<ref> Marquart 1895, 495 </ref> As a Persian military commander he was killed at the [[Battle of Granicus]] fighting [[Alexander the Great]].<ref> [[Arrian]] 1.16.3 </ref><ref> [[Diodorus]] 17.21.3 </ref>
The victorious Alexander appointed [[Abistamenes]] in his place.<ref> Arrian 2.4.2 </ref><ref> [[Quintus Curtius Rufus|Curtius Rufus]] 3.4.1 </ref>
